WEBVTT

00:00.354 --> 00:06.930
Last week we left Jesus in the basement of the high priest's chaiaphas.

00:08.066 --> 00:14.135
And we left him there after he had been arrested and beat and flogged.

00:14.515 --> 00:21.645
And after he told Peter that if you live by the sword, you die by the sword.

00:21.746 --> 00:36.146
And after Peter denied Jesus and the cockroach twice, and after the servant girl identified Peter as one of those followers of Jesus.

00:39.042 --> 00:40.884
There was chaos in the land.

00:42.667 --> 00:44.449
Nothing was as it should have been.

00:44.469 --> 00:51.118
And yet this was in the middle of a religious festival called the Passover.

00:53.942 --> 01:08.882
And at the festival, the governor of Rome and of Jerusalem at that time, he was to give a Paschal lamb to return one of the prisoners.

01:10.242 --> 01:19.095
to the gathered people and to absolve them of their crimes, to release them from their sin.

01:21.238 --> 01:38.322
And the people gathered and their choices that year were insurrectionist, rioting the murderous man who, well, he just didn't seem to be able to get it together.

01:42.594 --> 02:03.346
And then there was Jesus, Mary's baby, born in Bethlehem under that star where the wise people came and they looked at him and they said, surely this is the Messiah, the one who has come to save.

02:06.050 --> 02:23.017
The other choice was this Jesus who had traveled with 12 disciples teaching them of all the things that God was about to do to set the people free and make the blind to see, to heal the land.

02:26.503 --> 02:33.714
There was this Jesus who broke bread with the disciples just a few hours before.

02:35.682 --> 02:39.287
at the Passover mill and he changed it a little bit.

02:39.387 --> 02:42.391
He said, I'm going to wash your feet.

02:45.055 --> 02:51.463
And unless I wash your feet, you cannot be with me in paradise.

02:54.848 --> 03:05.522
And then he gave them bread and he said to them, take this bread and eat for this is my body, given for you.

03:06.434 --> 03:14.745
And every time you do this, every time you rehearse this, every time you re-enact this, do it in remembrance of me.

03:18.950 --> 03:21.653
The other choice was this Jesus who took the cup.

03:23.816 --> 03:25.879
It would have been wine then, Dr. Bob.

03:27.020 --> 03:34.610
He took the cup of wine and he gave it to his disciples and he said, drink from this all of you.

03:36.994 --> 03:55.521
This is the cup of the new covenant poured out for you and for many for the forgiveness of sins so that you can go and forgive others since.

03:59.487 --> 04:01.390
Do you remember the prayer that Jesus prayed?

04:01.430 --> 04:06.738
He prayed it so much that he prayed it in the garden of Gethsemane when he was headed to his death.

04:08.930 --> 04:13.376
He said, forgive us our trespasses.

04:14.278 --> 04:26.876
Some of you remember, forgive us our debts at the same measure that we forgive the trespasses of others.

04:32.544 --> 04:33.265
Did you hear that?

04:34.767 --> 04:36.530
Forgive our sins, oh God.

04:38.114 --> 04:41.739
at the same measure that we forgive the sins of other people.

04:53.718 --> 04:55.180
The time of trial has come.

04:58.845 --> 05:01.970
And Jesus and Barabbas stand before Pilate.

05:03.970 --> 05:11.743
And in the Gospel of Matthew, the 27th chapter, starting in the 15th verse, we hear these words.

05:13.726 --> 05:25.926
Now at the festival, the governor was accustomed to release a prisoner for the crowd, anyone whom they wanted.

05:27.589 --> 05:30.834
At that time, they had a notorious

05:31.138 --> 05:34.703
notorious prisoner called Jesus Barabbas.

05:36.225 --> 05:42.915
So after they had gathered, Pilate said to them, whom do you want me to release for you, Jesus?

05:43.656 --> 05:47.322
Jesus Barabbas or Jesus who was called the Messiah?

05:49.244 --> 05:54.152
For he realized that it was out of jealousy that they had handed him over.

05:55.894 --> 05:58.578
While he was sitting on the judgment seat,

05:59.522 --> 06:05.653
His wife sent word to him, have nothing to do with that innocent man.

06:05.773 --> 06:11.703
For today I have suffered a great deal because of a dream about him.

06:11.723 --> 06:20.599
Now the chief priests and the elders persuaded the crowds to ask for Barabbas and to have Jesus killed.

06:22.963 --> 06:24.786
The governor again said to them,

06:25.666 --> 06:29.511
Which of the two do you want me to release for you?"

06:32.475 --> 06:33.716
And they said, Barabbas.

06:36.620 --> 06:42.768
Pilate said to them, then what should I do with Jesus who is called the Messiah?

06:45.391 --> 06:48.295
All of them said, let him be crucified.

06:48.555 --> 06:49.056
Hear that.

06:49.757 --> 06:53.842
All of them said, let him be crucified.

06:56.706 --> 06:59.650
Then he asked, why?

07:00.611 --> 07:02.113
What evil has he done?

07:02.173 --> 07:08.220
But they shouted all the more, let him be crucified.

07:11.063 --> 07:26.322
So when Pilate saw that he could do nothing, but rather that a riot was beginning, he took some water and washed his hands before the crowd, saying, I am innocent of this man's blood.

07:28.482 --> 07:40.301
see to it yourselves, then the people as a whole answered, his blood beyond us and our children.

07:42.164 --> 07:44.568
So he released Barabbas for them.

07:44.608 --> 07:56.146
And after flogging Jesus, he handed him over to be crucified.

08:09.826 --> 08:12.950
This is the word of God for the people of God.

08:12.990 --> 08:15.534
Thanks be to God.

08:15.574 --> 08:20.400
Lord, we've come expecting a word from you, so speak now.

08:21.802 --> 08:28.652
For your servants are listening, allow your Holy Spirit to fall fresh on us so that the Holy Spirit preacher shall come.

08:30.033 --> 08:32.657
Hide this your servant behind that old rugged cross.

08:34.179 --> 08:39.346
So did everything that is said and everything that is done come straight from you, O God.

08:40.898 --> 08:45.082
This is your servant's prayer in the name of Jesus the Christ, we pray.

08:45.122 --> 08:47.665
Amen.

08:49.687 --> 08:51.849
They handed him over to be crucified.

08:55.052 --> 09:08.466
In the Gospel of Matthew, we understand that the Gospel writer is a little different from Mark and Luke because Matthew is trying to pull everybody together.

09:09.986 --> 09:19.244
Matthew includes and highlights Jewish worship traditions as a part of the gospel that he writes.

09:19.344 --> 09:26.258
And we see that in this text today through the hand washing of Pilate.

09:27.650 --> 09:30.694
Hand washing was a worship custom.

09:30.714 --> 09:41.929
When you came into the temple, you washed your hands as a sign that you were being made clean in Jesus Christ.

09:46.496 --> 09:47.697
Pilot washed his hands.

09:49.359 --> 09:52.544
And he said, I am innocent of this man's blood.

09:54.947 --> 09:57.170
You do this yourselves.

09:58.018 --> 10:02.669
In other words, this is on you.

10:06.418 --> 10:14.216
I remember years ago we sat down to eat dinner one night and my mom put our least favorite meal in front of us.

10:14.818 --> 10:16.722
Dr. Bob, it was a salad.

10:19.170 --> 10:24.540
And I remember it so vividly, there was French dressing on this salad.

10:25.121 --> 10:29.429
And I was upset because we were all out of ranch or blue cheese.

10:30.270 --> 10:35.019
And French was the only dressing that was available.

10:37.022 --> 10:40.108
And mom doused the salad in French dressing.

10:40.148 --> 10:43.474
Oh, did I tell you I can't stand French dressing?

10:49.538 --> 10:51.640
My brother and I sat there and looked at it.

10:53.302 --> 10:59.289
Mom ran upstairs to get ready for some meeting at church, and we were supposed to eat and be ready by the time she came back down.

11:02.152 --> 11:02.893
We looked at it.

11:05.356 --> 11:06.577
I said, Jason, we better eat.

11:06.697 --> 11:07.698
We're gonna get in trouble.

11:09.961 --> 11:10.722
We looked at it.

11:14.346 --> 11:16.128
Jason, we better eat.

11:17.169 --> 11:18.290
We're gonna get in trouble.

11:20.194 --> 11:21.996
Lisa, I picked at that salad.

11:24.779 --> 11:25.861
Picked at it some more.

11:27.282 --> 11:28.344
Picked at it some more.

11:30.807 --> 11:33.390
Till it was almost gone, Miss Ruby.

11:36.233 --> 11:39.577
But my brother, he was having none of this.

11:40.878 --> 11:43.922
He was not going to eat lettuce for dinner.

11:44.930 --> 11:52.018
He did not care what dressing was on it, that cucumbers were in it, cucumbers were our favorite.

11:52.418 --> 11:53.559
He did not care.

11:53.800 --> 11:56.342
He was not eating lettuce for dinner.

11:57.744 --> 12:01.728
And mom came downstairs and she noticed that not much of the food had been eaten.

12:02.189 --> 12:05.112
And she said, you better eat, that's all you're getting.

12:05.172 --> 12:07.835
And when I come back down here, be ready to go.

12:07.875 --> 12:14.482
Well, we weren't ready to go.

12:15.394 --> 12:22.302
when she came back down, I was still picking at my food and Jason dumped his in the trash can.

12:27.148 --> 12:32.574
I don't know how moms know, but they just know.

12:32.594 --> 12:38.761
Do you know Maya, the first thing she did when she came down those stairs was to look in the trash can.

12:41.485 --> 12:42.706
She said, who did this?

12:44.770 --> 12:45.411
It wasn't me.

12:47.153 --> 12:49.235
And do you know my brother had the nerve to say?

12:49.295 --> 12:50.777
It wasn't me.

12:55.162 --> 12:58.485
And my mom, she said, you're going to tell me who did it.

12:58.565 --> 13:00.548
You're going to, somebody's going to fess up here.

13:00.628 --> 13:02.029
You don't lie in my house.

13:02.049 --> 13:03.111
You don't tell stories.

13:03.371 --> 13:04.712
Now you couldn't say lie then.

13:04.973 --> 13:07.075
You don't tell stories in my house.

13:08.737 --> 13:10.459
And you certainly don't tell stories to me.

13:11.059 --> 13:13.362
Who put the lettuce in the trash can?

13:14.658 --> 13:17.342
Mom, it was not me, it was not me.

13:19.004 --> 13:20.947
And my brother just looked down and shook his head.

13:20.987 --> 13:27.796
She said, fine then, both of you are punished.

13:29.058 --> 13:40.434
I was so upset, Lisa, I was fit to be tied beyond, because you know, the worst thing that could happen to me was to get in trouble for something that I did not do.

13:42.818 --> 13:45.401
I was so angry with my brother.

13:45.421 --> 13:48.164
I was so angry with my mother.

13:52.309 --> 14:00.559
But mostly my feelings were hurt because my mother did not know that it was not me.

14:05.565 --> 14:09.970
Luckily, we had a kind of mother who punished you at night and she forgot about it by the morning.

14:10.690 --> 14:13.313
And so it wasn't a long punishment.

14:13.614 --> 14:16.498
But till this day, I'm still upset about it.

14:16.778 --> 14:18.140
I'm still holding on to it.

14:18.160 --> 14:21.344
Dr. Bob, I think I need to go and talk to Jesus about this.

14:30.196 --> 14:32.358
Have you ever gotten in trouble for something you didn't do?

14:32.378 --> 14:38.226
How did it feel?

14:42.530 --> 14:43.231
Did you like it?

14:45.256 --> 14:46.378
Was it warm and fuzzy?

14:48.122 --> 14:49.484
Was it something to celebrate?

14:49.524 --> 14:53.934
And if it was public, did it bring you any shame?

14:53.974 --> 15:03.794
Shame that somebody could think that you would do such a thing.

15:04.994 --> 15:12.354
See, the author of our study says that there's a difference between shame and guilt, and we get the mixed up.

15:12.975 --> 15:16.104
Shame means that we are bad.

15:16.605 --> 15:19.954
Guilt means that we did something that was bad.

15:20.706 --> 15:29.174
And so many times if we get in trouble for something we didn't do, we allow it to frame us.

15:29.534 --> 15:32.857
We allow it to become our identity.

15:32.897 --> 15:36.161
We allow it to bring us shame.

15:36.221 --> 15:41.706
She thinks I'm a bad person.

15:43.688 --> 15:49.573
She thinks I put the salad in the trash can.

15:49.593 --> 15:50.514
They think

15:51.202 --> 15:52.543
I murdered somebody.

15:55.947 --> 16:03.776
They think healing is worth death.

16:07.500 --> 16:20.434
Can you imagine the shame brought about that, that Barabbas, Jesus, Barabbas and Jesus, the Messiah stood next to each other in this public forum and there showed up shame.

16:22.562 --> 16:30.472
Every crime of Jesus Barabbas was listed for all of the people to see and hear.

16:30.532 --> 16:35.279
And it was called out crime by crime by crime.

16:35.639 --> 16:45.632
And this wasn't the first time that Jesus Barabbas would have stood before a crowd with his crimes listed because he was notorious.

16:47.755 --> 16:50.258
That meant he was a chronic offender.

16:50.466 --> 16:58.847
that people knew of him as a murderer just because just when his name was called.

17:01.554 --> 17:07.730
Can you imagine walking around with a title just because you show up?

17:08.386 --> 17:11.430
Somebody has labeled you lazy.

17:12.051 --> 17:14.834
Somebody has labeled you stupid.

17:15.355 --> 17:18.318
Somebody has labeled you unkind.

17:18.899 --> 17:22.844
Somebody has labeled you not good at something.

17:23.225 --> 17:30.674
The amount of shame that brings on, some people begin to live into those titles.

17:34.338 --> 17:43.712
I was talking to a gentleman the other day who had just gotten out of federal crime, 30 years in federal prison because he was in the wrong place at the wrong time.

17:46.395 --> 17:54.167
He was with a friend who shot somebody during a burglary and they both went to prison.

17:56.230 --> 17:59.314
He got 30 years, his friends got life.

18:01.570 --> 18:04.613
and he was walking around with a smile on his face.

18:05.775 --> 18:07.437
And I said, how can you be smiling?

18:07.457 --> 18:10.240
He said, preach I'm out.

18:10.260 --> 18:13.684
I said, but you did 30 years and you didn't do the shooting.

18:13.984 --> 18:18.389
He said, I know Pastor, but I worked through my shame.

18:20.772 --> 18:22.253
He said, I shouldn't have been there.

18:23.014 --> 18:27.740
My grandma told me to stay home, but I went anyway.

18:28.100 --> 18:29.842
I was disobedient.

18:30.754 --> 18:37.221
And I was shamed that I was disobedient because grandma told me this would happen.

18:45.349 --> 18:46.290
What is your shame?

18:56.360 --> 18:58.482
What is it that you have taken on?

19:00.354 --> 19:01.718
that is not yours to bear.

19:07.312 --> 19:12.546
Mine was my mom thinks that I threw that in the trash, that I'm wasteful and that I'm a liar.

19:12.566 --> 19:17.138
I don't want her to think that about me.

19:21.058 --> 19:31.049
And Barabbas, what we learn about Barabbas in history is that Barabbas actually might not have been as bad as a guy as we thought.

19:31.109 --> 19:38.657
He was walking in the historical footsteps of another man called Judas Barabbas.

19:39.678 --> 19:47.026
And Judas Barabbas led the Greeks into freedom through an insurrection.

19:49.698 --> 19:54.023
of slavery and into the light.

19:55.665 --> 20:00.591
And what we learned was that this Barabbas, Jesus' Barabbas, was trying to do the same thing.

20:00.932 --> 20:12.946
He was trying to lead people out of Roman rule and into freedom through insurrection and resulting murder.

20:15.234 --> 20:20.562
Imagine the shame when he stood up there and said and looked his mother in the face.

20:22.064 --> 20:26.411
And they called him a notorious murderer when he was trying to help his people get free.

20:34.303 --> 20:36.146
Imagine the shame of Jesus.

20:36.578 --> 20:50.434
The human Jesus who knows his purpose and his plan, but is still human at this point and is standing in front of his mother, has done nothing wrong.

20:54.178 --> 21:00.946
And yet they're saying release this bravest and kill that Jesus.

21:02.946 --> 21:12.884
And the text says over and over again, all of them, the whole of the gathered crowd, everybody there was on one accord.

21:12.924 --> 21:19.856
Let Berevis go crucify Jesus.

21:26.327 --> 21:27.890
We sit in this shame.

21:28.898 --> 21:43.301
We sit in the consequences of our actions, we sit in our choices, and we wonder if we have become these things instead of these things being choices that we made.

21:46.386 --> 21:56.722
I've seen so many people where they let their choices define who they are instead of a timeline in their life.

21:57.602 --> 22:03.874
And we condemn people to that kind of shamefulness as well.

22:04.215 --> 22:07.942
We say out loud, shame on you.

22:11.469 --> 22:14.354
And in doing so, we bind people up.

22:15.426 --> 22:21.636
We bind them up to a word, to a category, to a thing.

22:21.957 --> 22:27.446
And instead of calling them by their name, we call them by their shame.

22:32.894 --> 22:37.522
And the word of the Lord for us today is be free.

22:38.690 --> 22:42.655
Be free from whatever shame you have been carrying.

22:43.116 --> 22:46.660
Be free from whatever category they put you in.

22:47.181 --> 22:50.746
Be free from whatever they tried to make you.

22:50.766 --> 22:54.931
And remember that you are made in the image of God.

22:55.011 --> 22:59.717
And God says that you are beautifully and wonderfully made.

23:00.098 --> 23:06.386
God is pleased with you and by you just because you exist.

23:12.418 --> 23:15.688
There will always be a crowd that exists to condemn you.

23:15.728 --> 23:21.185
There will always be somebody who wants to shame you.

23:21.546 --> 23:26.802
There will always be somebody who wants you to be bound up.

23:27.042 --> 23:31.408
Because if you are free, then you get to live abundant life.

23:31.548 --> 23:34.932
If you are free, then you get to be healed.

23:35.032 --> 23:39.238
If you are free, then you get to be free indeed.

23:39.358 --> 23:43.844
And you get to enjoy the benefits of the crucifixion.

23:49.271 --> 23:51.474
Hear these words from the Gospel of Luke.

23:52.386 --> 23:58.632
There were two others also who were criminals and they were led away to be put to death with Jesus.

23:59.853 --> 24:06.640
And one of the criminals who hang there kept deriding him and saying, are you not the Messiah?

24:07.060 --> 24:09.663
Save yourself and us.

24:12.766 --> 24:17.630
But the other rebuked him saying, do not fear God.

24:17.670 --> 24:21.554
Do you not fear God?

24:21.986 --> 24:50.354
Since you are under the same sentence of condemnation And we indeed have been condemned justly for we are getting what we deserve for our demons But this man This man has done nothing wrong Then the criminal said Jesus

24:51.874 --> 24:52.675
Remember me.

24:54.778 --> 24:57.682
Jesus, remember me when you come into your kingdom.

24:57.742 --> 25:14.323
And Jesus replied, truly I tell you, today you will be with me in paradise.

25:18.629 --> 25:19.410
What will it be?

25:21.602 --> 25:25.086
Shame or freedom?

25:27.609 --> 25:37.561
Well, will it be abundant life or a sentence of condemnation?

25:39.003 --> 25:39.783
What will it be?

25:39.803 --> 25:48.754
I know who I am and whose I am or will it be that we allow somebody else to name us and call us shame?

25:53.154 --> 26:02.244
Whether you are Barabbas or whether you're as close to Jesus as we can get, you have a choice to make.

26:02.644 --> 26:11.654
You can be who God created you to be or you can be full of shame.

26:17.140 --> 26:19.442
Are you the criminal who

26:20.066 --> 26:23.870
poked at Jesus and derided him and said, you're up here with us, dude.

26:23.950 --> 26:24.911
Why don't you get down?

26:24.991 --> 26:27.573
You're supposed to be so big and bad.

26:27.593 --> 26:33.659
Almighty or the one on the other hand.

26:33.719 --> 26:38.544
We know better.

26:41.227 --> 26:42.808
We're in the same situation.

26:44.530 --> 26:45.851
We're on the same planet.

26:47.332 --> 26:48.914
We live in the same city.

26:50.018 --> 26:51.640
We live with the same stuff.

26:53.101 --> 26:59.788
Your zip code might have tree-lined streets, and my zip code might have some trash on the ground, but we are the same.

27:09.238 --> 27:10.379
Jesus, remember us.

27:15.884 --> 27:17.426
Remind us of our names.

27:20.514 --> 27:30.210
Take away our shame and allow us into your paradise.

27:37.723 --> 27:44.114
In the name of the Father, the Son and the Holy Spirit, we pray, amen.

